p at the Bethpage Black Course, Farmingdale, New\u202fYork. Picture date: Sunday\u202fSeptember\u202f28,\u202f2025.  \n3CR820G – New\u202fYork,\u202fUSA.\u202f29th\u202fSep,\u202f2025. George\u202fClooney and Amal\u202fClooney attend the Jay\u202fKelly red carpet during the 63rd New\u202fYork Film Festival at Alice\u202fTully\u202fHall in New\u202fYork, NY on September\u202f29,\u202f2025. (Photo by Efren\u202fLandaos/Sipa\u202fUSA)  \n3CPF5EE – Jamnagar, Gujarat, India.\u202f25th\u202fSep,\u202f2025. Devotees perform the Shiva\u202fTandav\u202fRaas, a ritual folk dance dedicated to Lord\u202fShiva, as part of Navratri festivities. (©\u202fSaurabh\u202fSirohiya/ZUMA\u202fPress\u202fWire) – Editorial use only.  \n3CR0084 – Newcastle’s Nick\u202fWoltemade, front, challenges for the ball with Arsenal’s Gabriel during the English Premier League soccer match between Newcastle and Arsenal at St\u202fJames\u202fPark, Newcastle upon Tyne, Sunday,\u202fSept.\u202f28,\u202f2025. (AP Photo/Jon\u202fSuper)  \n3CR86Y4 – Dwayne\u202fJohnson, left, star of\u202fThe\u202fSmashing\u202fMachine, poses with former wrestler and mixed martial artist Mark\u202fColeman at the premiere of the film, Monday,\u202fSept.\u202f29,\u202f2025, at the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences in Beverly Hills, Calif. (AP Photo/Chris\u202fPizzello)  \n3CRDJD6 – Carlos\u202fAlcaraz of Spain holds the victors trophy after winning the men’s singles title at the Japan Open tennis tournament at Ariake\u202fColiseum in Tokyo on\u202fSept.\u202f30,\u202f2025. (Kyodo)  \n3CRETJN – The Princess Royal views Ukrainian war veterans relaxing in a salt‑therapy room at a rehabilitation centre in Kyiv, after making a surprise trip to Ukraine in a show of solidarity with children and families facing the horrors of the Russian invasion. Picture date: Tuesday\u202fSeptember\u202f30,\u202f2025.  \n\n**Entry containing all four names (King\u202fCharles\u202fIII, Queen\u202fCamilla, Donald\u202fTrump, Melania) – not fo